Marty Walsh, the former Labor Secretary, is being praised for his strong leadership and dedication to fighting for American workers. Under his guidance, the Department of Labor has helped workers recover from an economic downturn and strengthen their position in the workforce. Some of his notable achievements include securing a pay raise for rail workers, advocating for paid sick days for all workers, and promoting workplace protections. Walsh recognizes the importance of unions in creating a stronger society and improving the lives of working Americans. His work sets a model for future Labor Secretaries who prioritize the well-being of American workers.